<div class=3D"t-li1"><span class=3D"t-li">1)</span> <code>std::vector</code=
> is a sequence container that encapsulates dynamic size arrays.</div>
<div class=3D"t-li1"><span class=3D"t-li">2)</span> <code>std::pmr::vector<=
/code> is an alias template that uses a <a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.=
com/w/cpp/memory/polymorphic_allocator.html" title=3D"cpp/memory/polymorphi=
c allocator">polymorphic allocator</a>.</div>
<p>Except for the <a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/container/ve=
ctor_bool.html" title=3D"cpp/container/vector bool"><code>std::vector&lt;bo=
ol&gt;</code></a> partial specialization, the elements are stored contiguou=
sly, which means that elements can be accessed not only through iterators, =
but also using offsets to regular pointers to elements. This means that a p=
ointer to an element of a vector may be passed to any function that expects=
 a pointer to an element of an array.
</p><p>The storage of the vector is handled automatically, being expanded a=
s needed. Vectors usually occupy more space than static arrays, because mor=
e memory is allocated to handle future growth. This way a vector does not n=
eed to reallocate each time an element is inserted, but only when the addit=
ional memory is exhausted. The total amount of allocated memory can be quer=
ied using <span class=3D"t-lc"><a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp=
/container/vector/capacity.html" title=3D"cpp/container/vector/capacity">ca=
pacity()</a></span> function. Extra memory can be returned to the system vi=
a a call to <span class=3D"t-lc"><a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.com/w/c=
pp/container/vector/shrink_to_fit.html" title=3D"cpp/container/vector/shrin=
k to fit">shrink_to_fit()</a></span><sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/container/vector.html#cite=
_note-1">[1]</a></sup>.
</p><p>Reallocations are usually costly operations in terms of performance.=
 The <span class=3D"t-lc"><a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/cont=
ainer/vector/reserve.html" title=3D"cpp/container/vector/reserve">reserve()=
</a></span> function can be used to eliminate reallocations if the number o=
f elements is known beforehand.
</p><p>The complexity (efficiency) of common operations on vectors is as fo=
llows:
</p>
<ul><li> Random access - constant <span class=3D"texhtml" style=3D"white-sp=
ace: nowrap;">=F0=9D=93=9E(1)</span>.
</li><li> Insertion or removal of elements at the end - amortized constant =
<span class=3D"texhtml" style=3D"white-space: nowrap;">=F0=9D=93=9E(1)</spa=
n>.
</li><li> Insertion or removal of elements - linear in the distance to the =
end of the vector <span class=3D"texhtml" style=3D"white-space: nowrap;">=
=F0=9D=93=9E(n)</span>.
</li></ul>
<p><code>std::vector</code> (for <code>T</code> other than <span class=3D"m=
w-geshi cpp source-cpp"><span class=3D"kw4">bool</span></span>) meets the r=
equirements of <a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/named_req/Conta=
iner.html" title=3D"cpp/named req/Container"><span style=3D"font-family: Ge=
orgia, 'DejaVu Serif', serif; font-style:italic">Container</span></a><span =
class=3D"t-rev-inl t-since-cxx11"><span>, <a href=3D"https://en.cppreferenc=
e.com/w/cpp/named_req/AllocatorAwareContainer.html" title=3D"cpp/named req/=
AllocatorAwareContainer"><span style=3D"font-family: Georgia, 'DejaVu Serif=
', serif; font-style:italic">AllocatorAwareContainer</span></a></span><span=
><span class=3D"t-mark-rev t-since-cxx11">(since C++11)</span></span></span=
>, <a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/named_req/SequenceContainer=
.html" title=3D"cpp/named req/SequenceContainer"><span style=3D"font-family=
: Georgia, 'DejaVu Serif', serif; font-style:italic">SequenceContainer</spa=
n></a><span class=3D"t-rev-inl t-since-cxx17"><span>, <a href=3D"https://en=
.cppreference.com/w/cpp/named_req/ContiguousContainer.html" title=3D"cpp/na=
med req/ContiguousContainer"><span style=3D"font-family: Georgia, 'DejaVu S=
erif', serif; font-style:italic">ContiguousContainer</span></a></span><span=
><span class=3D"t-mark-rev t-since-cxx17">(since C++17)</span></span></span=
> and <a href=3D"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/named_req/ReversibleCont=
ainer.html" title=3D"cpp/named req/ReversibleContainer"><span style=3D"font=
-family: Georgia, 'DejaVu Serif', serif; font-style:italic">ReversibleConta=
iner</span></a>.
</p>
